National Security Advisor Thomas E. Donilon will be traveling to China and Japan to meet with senior officials and discuss various topics. In China, he will meet with State Councilor Dai Bingguo to discuss the current and future state of U.S.-China relations, as well as cooperation on regional and global challenges such as nonproliferation, regional security in Asia and the Middle East, and global economic growth. In Japan, Mr. Donilon will have consultations with senior Japanese officials on U.S.-Japan security cooperation, bilateral issues, and other regional and global challenges.